<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause id="_855368f2-92db-4fd0-85c3-1223d7324d4f" outputclass="ncc-clause" variation="SA"><sptc>I3D14</sptc><title id="_1f216ea4-de3d-48ba-bb01-193b74acca0c">Direction signs</title><subclause id="_183749b5-c9cc-4784-b5e9-bba5c256c8c1" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_4f8fae6c-0bcc-4ac3-8847-6ee603d8ce3b">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>In a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/2abe2d62-a871-4509-969b-2425466626a4/1271_2.5.0.xml#_f68a626d-6a81-4785-95fa-c032c987c28e" id="_2a8a221d-72fe-4292-bc0b-4d2e73ed84e8" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">farm building</xref>, if an exit is not readily apparent to persons occupying or visiting the building, exit signs complying with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/2abe2d62-a871-4509-969b-2425466626a4/10698_0.2.0.xml#_12a76732-402b-4334-ad74-f5339bf514ce" id="_a262d4ca-8d7d-46a2-8ec8-4c115fc01fc9" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="ncc-clause">SA I3D15</xref> must installed in appropriate positions in corridors, hallways, lobbies and the like, indicating the direction to a required exit.</p></subclause></clause>